Somethingreek is something you should try if you ever drive down to Bay Ridge, Brooklyn. From the  moment you walk in the first thing you will notice is the beautiful interior decor of the restaurant. From the walls to the ceiling and the arrangement of the tables. One of the main reasons I wanted to go in was because of course I wanted to try the food but because I like the interior design of the restaurant. This is the perfect spot to take good pics of your food with a nice background. You can say this spot is IG ready. However the food isn't the healthiest food around Bay Ridge. I wouldn't say the food was exceptional. I wasn't impressed with the food, it was average. The service wasn't amazing and that was a bit of a let down. Parking wasn't great. But there's meter parking available. I would still recommend the restaurant but I probably wouldn't go back anytime soon. Overall Somethingreek is just another average restaurant with a lot of potential.

Ate there on a Saturday night. Service was great, but food was a huge disappointment and VERY expensive. Spinach pie app was served in a bowl - 6 tiny triangles, seemed like they might have been frozen. (Certainly not a pie) Horta was so over-cooked it was nearly pureed. I should have sent it back. Although the Greek salad and the Beet salad were good, the baklava dessert was very puny in size and too thin. One main course (fish), two appetizers, two salads and two sides (horta), one dessert, and 1 cocktail, and the check was over $170.00. Stars earned for service, ambience and salads. Too bad too- we really tried to like this place.
